# Adaptive layout

This scenario verifies that the picker redraws when the terminal width changes.
At narrow widths the session list and preview are stacked vertically; once the
terminal is wide enough they switch to a side-by-side layout.

    :bins jj cat

> [!NOTE]
> 'jj', and 'cat' are available.

    :t rename-session -t 0 runner (success)
    :$ jj git init alpha (exit: 0)
    :$ jj describe -R alpha -m "alpha commit" (exit: 0)
    :t new-session -d -s ui "sesh -r alpha" (success)
    :t resize-window -t ui:0 -x 120 -y 10 (success)
    :pane ui:0.0

This snapshot shows the narrow stacked layout, including the horizontal
separator between the session list and preview.

    :k alpha
    :snap "/\d{4}-\d{2}-\d{2} \d{2}:\d{2}:\d{1,2}/t" "/(?:@|○|◆)\s+([a-z]{8})/w" "/\b([0-9a-f]{8})\b/h"

```terminal
session: alpha
  1/3 | [C-r] repo: none | [C-n] new
▌  alpha                                    alpha                                                                      ┃
────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────
@  wwwwwwww (no email set) ttttttttttttttttttt hhhhhhhh
│  (empty) alpha commit
◆  wwwwwwww root() hhhhhhhh



```

After widening the terminal, the picker should redraw with the session list and
preview side by side.

    :t resize-window -t ui:0 -x 180 -y 10 (success)
    :snap "/\d{4}-\d{2}-\d{2} \d{2}:\d{2}:\d{1,2}/t" "/(?:@|○|◆)\s+([a-z]{8})/w" "/\b([0-9a-f]{8})\b/h"

```terminal
session: alpha                                                                                             ┃@  wwwwwwww (no email set) ttttttttttttttttttt hhhhhhhh
  1/3 | [C-r] repo: none | [C-n] new                                                                       ┃│  (empty) alpha commit
▌  alpha                                    alpha                                                          ┃◆  wwwwwwww root() hhhhhhhh
                                                                                                           ┃
                                                                                                           ┃
                                                                                                           ┃
                                                                                                           ┃
                                                                                                           ┃
                                                                                                           ┃
                                                                                                           ┃
```

